# .gitignore for Java 21 & IntelliJ IDEA

### IntelliJ IDEA ###
# Covers project-specific settings, module files, and output directories.
.idea/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
out/
atlassian-ide-plugin.xml

### Build Tools ###

## Maven ##
# Ignores Maven's build output directory and release plugin files.
target/
pom.xml.tag
pom.xml.releaseBackup
pom.xml.versionsBackup
pom.xml.next
release.properties
dependency-reduced-pom.xml

## Gradle ##
# Ignores Gradle's build output and cache directories.
.gradle/
build/
# The gradle-wrapper.jar is sometimes ignored to avoid committing binaries,
# but it's often recommended to commit it for reproducible builds.
# Uncomment the line below if you wish to ignore it.
# gradle-wrapper.jar

### Java & JVM ###
# Ignores compiled bytecode, package files, and JVM crash logs.
*.class
*.jar
*.war
*.ear
hs_err_pid*

### Logs & Temporary Files ###
# General log files and compressed archives that are often temporary.
*.log
*.log.*
*.zip
*.tar.gz
*.rar

### OS-Specific Files ###
# Ignores metadata files generated by macOS and Windows.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

### Sensitive Information ###
# It's a good practice to ignore files containing secrets or local configurations.
# Instead, commit a template file (e.g., application.properties.example).
*.env
application.properties
application.yml